-type="Heading" class="sc-jJMGnK evXokT pf-77_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gsWcmt grZHMV pf-79_">06.05: Juice<br></span></h3><p class="sc-fXazdy ujFwY pf-80_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gsWcmt grZHMV pf-82_">The diffuser is turned on and I go to the kitchen to make a healthy green juice in my slow juicer. I always try to use organic ingredients, but I still make sure to clean them well.</span></p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-83_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0277/5859/2073/t/3/assets/pf-b0707a9f--3F577EC80B5B49198A4CB9CE2A0F2F79-1-Edited_500x.jpg?v=1598800170" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0277/5859/2073/t/3/assets/pf-b0707a9f--3F577EC80B5B49198A4CB9CE2A0F2F79-1-Edited.jpg?v=1598800170 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0277/5859/2073/t/3/assets/pf-b0707a9f--3F577EC80B5B49198A4CB9CE2A0F2F79-1-Edited_500x.jpg?v=1598800170 320w" width="640" height="577" loading="lazy" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-ciSkZP bwSYJA pf-84_"/></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-85_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jJMGnK evXokT pf-86_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gsWcmt grZHMV pf-88_">Healthy Juice Recipe: Green Wellness<br></span></h3><p class="sc-fXazdy ujFwY pf-89_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gsWcmt grZHMV pf-91_">1 stalk of celery<br>1 lemon<br>1 handfull spinach<br>1 handfull kale<br>5 cm ginger<br><br>Run the ingredients through a slow juicer. If you do not have a slow juicer, use a normal blender with 100 ml of water, and strain out the water after blending. I then bring the juice over to my yoga mat.<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-lbVvki ghCdOs pf-92_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eirqVv dSzotL"><div class="sc-iwajpm kydRHc pf-93_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-94_"><div class="sc-iwajpm kydRHc pf-95_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-96_"><div class="sc-iwajpm kydRHc pf-97_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-98_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0277/5859/2073/t/3/assets/pf-489ca6b0--211C1F5A72E4453DB3F51BDAC920ED4C_500x.jpeg?v=1598799311" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0277/5859/2073/t/3/assets/pf-489ca6b0--211C1F5A72E4453DB3F51BDAC920ED4C.jpeg?v=1598799311 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0277/5859/2073/t/3/assets/pf-489ca6b0--211C1F5A72E4453DB3F51BDAC920ED4C_500x.jpeg?v=1598799311 320w" width="640" height="519" loading="lazy" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-ciSkZP bwSYJA pf-99_"/><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jJMGnK evXokT pf-100_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gsWcmt grZHMV pf-102_">06:15: Breath Work, Meditation, and Affirmation<br></span></h3><p class="sc-fXazdy ujFwY pf-103_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gsWcmt grZHMV pf-105_">I bring my juice and do my breathing exercise. A breathing exercise that works well in the morning is breathing slowly. Count to 4 while breathing in, and count to 5 when breathing out. A couple minutes of this, and you'll feel great
<br>
<br>For me, about 5 minutes of meditation is enough in the morning. My favourite form of meditation is affirmations, one sentence starting with "I am..." that you repeat in your head. 
<br><br><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">My Favourite Affirmations<br></span>I am fantastic<br>I am unique<br>I am calm<br>I am happy<br>I am good enough<br><br><span style="text-decoration-line: underline;">Meditation with affirmations: <br></span>1. Find a comfortable seated position
<br>2. Close your eyes
<br>3. Breath slowly and calmly through your nose
<br>4. For every inhalation, think of the words "I am..." 
<br>5. For every exhalation, think of your chosen word, ie. "...happy"
<br>6. Repeat as many times as you like
<br>7. Open your eyes
<br>8. Notice how you are feeling&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-lbVvki ghCdOs pf-106_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-eirqVv dSzotL"><div class="sc-iwajpm kydRHc pf-107_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-108_"><div class="sc-iwajpm kydRHc pf-109_ pf-r pf-c-cm" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-jffHpj jjTcTs pf-110_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jJMGnK evXokT pf-111_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gsWcmt grZHMV pf-113_">06.25: Self-Massage<br></span></h3><p class="sc-fXazdy ujFwY pf-114_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gsWcmt grZHMV pf-116_">To end my morning ritual, I use my yoga oil that is scented of rose and lavender. It's organic and gives nutrition to the skin and hair. I inhale the aroma of the oil and give myself a short massage, some days a neck massage, other days a foot massage. It's a nice reminder to be kind to yourself.
